-- Polish Stocks: Azoty Tarnow, Polimex-Mostostal Shares Are Active
-- B y   P i o t r   B u j n i c k i
-- 2012-07-13T09:31:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-13/polish-stocks-azoty-tarnow-polimex-mostostal-shares-are-active.html
Poland’s  WIG20 Index (WIG20)  advanced 1
percent to 2,176.36 at 11:07 a.m. in Warsaw, paring its decline
for the week to 4.1 percent.  The following are among the most active stocks on the
 Warsaw Stock Exchange  today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Azoty Tarnow (ATT PW), Poland’s largest chemicals maker,
jumped 4 percent to 37.44 zloty, the steepest gain in two weeks
after OAO Acron of Russia increased its bid for the company to
45 zloty from 36 zloty a share.  Polimex-Mostostal SA (PXM)  , the country’s second-largest
builder, declined 3.8 percent to 0.77 zloty, falling for a
second day, after saying it started talks with creditors to
extend repayment of bonds and loans.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Piotr Bujnicki in Warsaw 
